<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,770,1337]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,519,1058,1084]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vogel" authorityYear="1837" box="[520,816,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Platymiscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floribundum">
<emphasis box="[520,816,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Platymiscium floribundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an endemic species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1098,1169,1058,1084]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, present in the Northeast, Midwest, Southeast and South regions associated with the domains of the Caatinga, Cerrado and Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Flora do Brasil" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" refId="ref15971" refString="Flora do Brasil 2020 (2020) Fabaceae. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. [http: // reflora. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 115]" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry box="[172,239,1130,1156]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Popularly known as jacarandá do litoral, the species also has records in 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1227,1130,1156]" name="Bolivia" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1284,1451,1130,1156]" name="French Guiana" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(INCT - Virtual Herbarium of Flora and Fungi).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,770,1337]" box="[189,741,1202,1228]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,1202,1228]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers in August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,770,1337]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,496,1238,1264]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vogel" authorityYear="1837" box="[496,803,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Platymiscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floribundum">
<emphasis box="[496,803,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Platymiscium floribundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized, mainly, by the arboreous habit, interpeciolar stipules, leaves opposite, imparipinnate with opposite leaflets, yellow corolla, papilionaceous, samara 
<typeStatus box="[136,184,1311,1337]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
fruit and seeds with black coat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
